cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper presents a method for checking local robustness in feed-forward neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "learning" (cs.LG). The method involves analyzing the polyhedral regions of the network, which is related to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of geometric projections is a computational technique that is often used in neural networks and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency of the method, which is related to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
